article.headline: Ohio 83, Marist 66
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Ohio's balanced offense and 56 percent shooting landed five players in double figures Saturday as the Bobcats opened their season with an 83-66 victory over Marist. Jerome Tillman, Leon Williams and Whitney Davis all had 16 points, Sonny Troutman had 14 and Kenneth van Kempen had 10. Tillman was just 3-of-7 from the field, but 10-of-12 at the line. Jared Jordan led Marist with 21 points, and Will Whittington had 19. Marist scored the first basket, a 3-pointer by Whittington, but a layup and free throw by Troutman tied the score. A steal and dunk by Troutman made it 5-3 with 14:52 to play, and Ohio led the rest of the way. The Bobcats took a 36-21 lead at halftime. Jordan's layup got Marist within eight with 9:12 to play, but Williams hit a jumper and two free throws to end the threat.
